ith his crew (positive teamwork)\n- solves problems extremely well? Actually D solves problems; C not listed. Wait earlier: \"Candidate C is known to be 100% reliable.\" and \"Candidate C creates a positive atmosphere with his crew.\" Good teamwork.\n\nCandidate D:\n- responds to unexpected events adequately (adaptability)\n- can concentrate very well (focus)\n- solves problems extremely well (problem solving)\n- takes responsibility seriously (responsibility)\n- regarded as arrogant (negative)\n- weak leadership skills (weakness)\n- know-it-all, hot temper (negative)\n- also earlier: \"Candidate D is regarded as arrogant.\" and \"relatively weak leadership skills.\"\n\nNow evaluate against criteria: reliability, technical competence, calmness, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nWe need to weigh strengths vs weaknesses. Candidate C seems strong: 100% reliable, calm in crisis, good technical, creates positive atmosphere, quick correct decisions. Weaknesses: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education. But positive crew atmosphere may offset communication difficulty? Egocentric may conflict with positive atmosphere. Mixed.\n\nCandidate B: reliable (conscientious), handles stress, good weather assessment, computer skills. Weaknesses: pretentious, grumpy, uncooperative, wrong tone. Teamwork poor.\n\nCandidate A: leadership qualities, anticipates danger, spatial vision, sees complex connections. Weaknesses: unfriendly, unorganized, poor at criticism. Teamwork issues.\n\nCandidate D: strong problem solving, responsibility, concentration, adaptability. Weaknesses: arrogant, weak leadership, know-it-all, hot temper. Teamwork lacking.\n\nThus candidate C appears most balanced: reliability, calm, decision-making, positive crew atmosphere. Communication difficulty and egocentric are concerns but positive atmosphere suggests ability to work with crew. Also not willing to further education may affect long-term development.\n\nCandidate B also reliable but poor teamwork.\n\nCandidate A has leadership but poor interpersonal.\n\nCandidate D strong technical but poor leadership.\n\nThus likely candidate C is best.\n\nWe should maybe ask others about any additional positive teamwork info for A or D, but we have already asked. Could ask about any further strengths for A's teamwork/communication beyond leadership? But we have already asked. Could ask about any additional strengths for D's teamwork? Already asked. So we have all info.\n\nNow produce public message: summarize evaluation, note trade-offs, state vote for Candidate C, with confidence maybe 70%.\n\nAlso include open questions: maybe about willingness to further education for C, but we have that.\n\nLet's craft."}
